==English==
===Noun===
'''formalism'''
#A computational paradigm for a theory: one out of a plurality of alternative computational paradigms for the given theory.
#In literature: an approach to interpretation and/or evaluation focused on the (usually linguistic) structure of a literary work rather than on the contexts of its origin or reception.
#In music: the endency to elevate formal above expressive value in music, as in Neoclassical music.
